Partners
& Resources

We only partner with trusted providers in order to bring you
the best payment solutions for your business.

Free Quote
Contact Sales

Dynamic Merchant Solutions provides industry-leading service and support to businesses like yours. Whether you’re looking for cutting-edge payment solutions and hardware, the best rates, or 24/7 customer service from a real person, Dynamic Merchant Solutions is your go-to provider.

First American Payment Systems

First American Payment Systems (FAPS) is a registered ISO of Fifth Third Bank, Wells Fargo Bank and Metabank. The company was founded in 1990 and is
currently based in Fort Worth, Texas. In January 2016, First American Payment Systems acquired the entire independent sales office portfolio of Chase
Commerce Solutions. First American Payment Systems is a merchant account provider which offers payment solutions including mobile, in-person and e-
commerce options.

goEmerchant

goEmerchant is an online payment processing company founded in 1995, which acts primarily as a reseller of First American Payment Systems (FAPS). goEmerchant provides merchants with the tools and technology necessary to accept and process payments online and in-store, including software for POS systems and mobile processing, payment page builder, staff management, gift card and loyalty programs, and more.

Authorize.net

As a pioneer in e-commerce, Authorize.net has paved the way for online processing. With a variety of options for your processing needs, authorize net makes it simple and easy for you to accept credit cards online. Dynamic Merchant Solutions is an authorized reseller of authorize.net, and combines its Chase processing with the innovative Autorize.net gateway.

PCI – DDS

The Payment Card Industry Data Security Standard (PCI DSS) is a worldwide information security standard defined by the Payment Card Industry Security Standards Council. The standard was created to help payment card industry organizations that process card payments prevent credit card fraud through increased controls around data and its exposure to compromise. The standard applies to all organizations that hold, process, or exchange cardholder information from any card branded with the logo of one of the card brands.

Interchange Rates

Interchange rates are the fees that merchants pay to the card-issuing banks in order to process credit card payments. These fees are made up of a percentage of the customer’s purchase, plus a flat fee per transaction. These rates apply to all credit card networks—Visa, Mastercard, Discover and American Express. Some transactions, such as online purchases, have higher rates than in-person transactions.

Get 24 hour support from a real person

When you need support from Dynamic Merchant Solutions, you have a real person available to you, 24/7. Whether you have a billing question or need tech support, you have access to the best customer service.

Get Started Today

Transform your business idea into a custom mobile app.

Let our experts create a mobile app specifically for your business and start selling directly to your customers.
